## Overview

This notebook covers the complete dataset analysis phase for the CIC-IDS2018 intrusion detection dataset. The analysis focuses on the `Flow IAT Mean` (inter-arrival time) feature as the primary temporal signal, combined with time-of-day slot extraction, to investigate whether timing behavior alone can distinguish benign from attack traffic.

---

## Dataset Source

```
Platform  : Kaggle
Slug      : solarmainframe/ids-intrusion-csv
Load path : /kaggle/input/ids-intrusion-csv/
Primary file used : 02-21-2018.csv (mixed benign + attack traffic)
```

**Dataset day reference:**

| File | Content | Role |
|---|---|---|
| 02-21-2018.csv | Mixed benign + DDoS | Primary analysis + training |
| 02-16-2018.csv | DDoS-heavy | Test set |
| 03-01-2018.csv | Botnet | Generalization test |
| 02-28-2018.csv | Mixed | Optional validation |

